            "answer_text": "Sure he thought of then as Scandinavian. German propaganda used Viking imagery all the time and so had to embrace Scandinavian culture. Some of the images called on Scandinavians fight alongside Germany against the USSR.     Add to that the fact that the Finns were allied with Hitler early on (mostly out of fear of the USSR). And don\u2019t forget unit like 5th SS Panzer Division Wiking. Hitler\u2019s rhetoric made it so he sort of had to embrace Scandinavian, which made his invasion of Norway extra problematic as it called on him to fight a people he could not use his usual demeaning propaganda against. ",
